ALIGN=CENTER>The Epistle of Paul to the Colossians</H2></CENTER><P><A           
HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5  
WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 4</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>Masters, give unto your servants    
that which is just and equal; knowing that ye also have a Master in heaven.</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>Continue in       
prayer, and watch in the same with thanksgiving;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD           
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>Withal praying also for us, that    
ELOHIYM would open unto us a door of utterance, to speak the mystery of         
MASHIYACH, for which I am also in bonds:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A     
NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>That I may make it manifest, as I ought to        
speak.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Walk in 
wisdom toward them that are without, redeeming the time.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Let your speech be alway with       
grace, seasoned with salt, that ye may know how ye ought to answer every        
man.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>All my    
state shall Tychicus declare unto you, who is a beloved brother, and a faithful 
minister and fellowservant in the ADONAY:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>Whom I have sent unto you for the same purpose,   
that he might know your estate, and comfort your hearts;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>With Onesimus, a faithful and       
beloved brother, who is one of you. They shall make known unto you all things   
which are done here.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4>    
</TD><TD><P>Aristarchus my fellowprisoner saluteth you, and Marcus, sister's    
son to Barnabas, (touching whom ye received commandments: if he come unto you,  
receive him;)</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>And Jesus, which is called Justus, who are of the circumcision. These only   
are my fellowworkers unto the kingdom of EL, which have been a comfort unto     
me.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>         
Epaphras, who is one of you, a servant of MASHIYACH, saluteth you, always       
labouring fervently for you in prayers, that ye may stand perfect and complete  
in all the will of ELOHIYM.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>    
13</H4></TD><TD><P>For I bear him record, that he hath a great zeal for you,    
and them that are in Laodicea, and them in Hierapolis.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Luke, the beloved physician, and  
Demas, greet you.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD>  
<TD><P>Salute the brethren which are in Laodicea, and Nymphas, and the church   
which is in his house.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4>  
</TD><TD><P>And when this epistle is read among you, cause that it be read also 
in the church of the Laodiceans; and that ye likewise read the epistle from     
Laodicea.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>   
And say to Archippus, Take heed to the ministry which thou hast received in the 
ADONAY, that thou fulfil it.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>   
18</H4></TD><TD><P>The salutation by the hand of me Paul. Remember my bonds.    
Grace be with you. Amen.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright    
